                 "contributingIntro":  "This project is open source. Contributions are welcome.",
                 "freshnessCopy":  "The dataset is refreshed periodically. Each refresh captures the latest merged PRs from tracked organizations. New contributors, projects, and PRs appear after the next successful refresh cycle.",
                 "faqEcosystemQuestion":  "Can I add a new ecosystem?",
                 "howCopy":  "The project periodically fetches merged pull request data from GitHub\u0027s public API for tracked organizations. The data is processed, aggregated, and served as static CSV files. The dashboard reads these files and renders the contribution layer in the browser.",
                 "collectionCopy":  "Data is collected through GitHub\u0027s public API using the Search endpoint for merged pull requests. The collection process is fully open-source and reproducible. Collection scripts reside in the repository for anyone to inspect or run independently.",
                 "contributingCopy":  "To add a new ecosystem, submit a pull request updating the collection configuration. To report issues, suggest features, or ask questions, open an issue on \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/alerodriargui/proof-of-contribution\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003eGitHub\u003c/a\u003e.",
                 "attributionCopy":  "Contributions are attributed to GitHub usernames as they appear in merged PR author fields. Bot accounts are identified and can be filtered out. GHOST вЂ” GitHub\u0027s placeholder for deleted or unavailable users вЂ” is also identified in the dataset.",
                 "technicalIntro":  "Architecture, local setup, and repository layout for developers.",
                 "repoCopy":  "The main application lives in \u003ccode\u003eapp/\u003c/code\u003e. Data collection scripts are in \u003ccode\u003escripts/\u003c/code\u003e. CSV data files are at the repository root. Locale files for i18n are in \u003ccode\u003eapp/locales/\u003c/code\u003e. The contributor detail page is at \u003ccode\u003econtributors/\u003c/code\u003e.",
                 "faqBotsQuestion":  "How are bot accounts handled?",
                 "limitationsCopy":  "This project measures merged PRs only. It does not track issues, comments, code reviews, or other forms of contribution. Additionally, only public repositories in tracked organizations are included. Data is as fresh as the last refresh cycle.",
